  "prompt": "How much money does YouTube make?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, YouTube's revenue is largely derived from advertising. In 2022, YouTube generated approximately $28.8 billion in ad revenue. This figure fluctuates year by year based on various factors including changes in ad spending, the number of active users, and content engagement.\n\nIn addition to ad revenue, YouTube also makes money from subscriptions, particularly through YouTube Premium, which offers an ad-free experience and access to exclusive content. The exact figures for overall revenue including subscriptions can vary.\n\nYouTube's parent company, Alphabet Inc. (which is also the parent company of Google), often provides updated financials in quarterly earnings reports, which can offer more recent figures on YouTube's performance.\n\nIf you are looking for the latest statistics, I recommend checking the most current financial disclosures from Alphabet or reliable news sources for updated information.",
